---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const serviceSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Service",
  "name": "Golf Course Advertising Revenue Partnership",
  "provider": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Sports Digital Network"
  },
  "description": "Add a revenue stream to your golf course with digital advertising screens. SDN handles everything — installation, ad sales, content. Zero cost.",
  "areaServed": {
    "@type": "Country",
    "name": "Canada"
  },
  "serviceType": "Golf Course Digital Display Partnership"
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Golf Course Advertising Revenue | Digital Signage for Clubhouses | SDN"
  description="Add a revenue stream to your golf course with digital advertising screens. SDN handles everything — installation, ad sales, content. Zero cost. Apply today."
  canonicalPath="/venues/golf/"
  schema={serviceSchema}
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <h1>Your clubhouse visitors are worth more than you think</h1>
    <p>SDN installs digital advertising screens in golf course clubhouses, sells the ad space, and shares the revenue with your course. You pay nothing.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="intro-section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="lead">Golf course clubhouses are one of the most under-monetized advertising environments in Canada. Your members and guests spend 30-60 minutes in the clubhouse before and after their rounds — eating, drinking, socializing, waiting for tee times, and browsing the pro shop.</p>
      <p>They're affluent, they're relaxed, and they're exactly the audience that premium brands want to reach. SDN helps you capture that value without any cost or effort from your team.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="why-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why golf courses are premium advertising venues</h2>
      <p>Golf course visitors represent one of the most desirable consumer demographics in Canadian advertising:</p>

      <div class="reasons-grid">
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>Affluence</h3>
          <p>The average Canadian golfer has a household income significantly above the national median. Members of private clubs skew even higher. This is an audience that makes premium purchasing decisions — vehicles, financial services, travel, luxury goods, real estate, and home improvement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>Dwell time</h3>
          <p>A round of golf takes 4+ hours, but the advertising opportunity is in the clubhouse. Members and guests spend 30-60 minutes pre-round (checking in, warming up, having coffee) and 30-60 minutes post-round (dining, socializing, using the bar). That's substantial time in front of our screens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>Receptivity</h3>
          <p>Golfers are in a relaxed, positive environment. Research consistently shows that consumers are more receptive to advertising messages when they're in a good mood and a comfortable setting. A golf clubhouse is exactly that.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reason-card">
          <h3>Repeat visitation</h3>
          <p>Regular members play 40-80+ rounds per year. Even casual visitors return multiple times per season. Advertisers get repeated exposure to the same high-value audience.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="install-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What SDN installs in your clubhouse</h2>
      <p>We install 1-3 screens per golf course, positioned where your members and guests spend time:</p>

      <div class="locations-grid">
        <div class="location-item">
          <strong>Main clubhouse lounge / bar area</strong>
          <span>where members gather before and after rounds</span>
        </div>
        <div class="location-item">
          <strong>Pro shop</strong>
          <span>where golfers browse equipment and check in</span>
        </div>
        <div class="location-item">
          <strong>Restaurant / dining area</strong>
          <span>where visitors sit for meals and drinks</span>
        </div>
        <div class="location-item">
          <strong>Hallway / entrance</strong>
          <span>high-traffic corridors</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>Screens are 65-inch commercial-grade 4K displays — the same professional hardware we install in our arena network. They're appropriate for the premium environment of a golf clubhouse.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What runs on the screens</h2>
      <p>Content is tailored for the golf environment:</p>

      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-item">
          <strong>Advertising (~50% of screen time)</strong>
          <p>Premium brand campaigns and local business ads relevant to your membership demographic</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-item">
          <strong>Weather</strong>
          <p>Current conditions and multi-day forecasts (golfers check weather constantly)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-item">
          <strong>Sports scores</strong>
          <p>PGA Tour leaderboards, NHL/MLB/NFL scores</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-item">
          <strong>Course information</strong>
          <p>Tee time availability, event schedules, tournament results</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-item">
          <strong>Clubhouse promotions</strong>
          <p>Your pro shop specials, dining features, membership offers</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="content-note">The content keeps the screens relevant and useful, which keeps eyes on them — and makes the advertising more effective.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="revenue-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Revenue for your course</h2>

      <div class="revenue-grid">
        <div class="revenue-card">
          <h3>How it works</h3>
          <p>SDN sells advertising inventory on your clubhouse screens to a mix of national brands and local businesses. You receive a guaranteed monthly revenue share — deposited to your account every month for the duration of our partnership.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="revenue-card">
          <h3>Who advertises at golf courses?</h3>
          <p>The premium demographics of golf course visitors attract advertisers from categories like:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Automotive — luxury and premium vehicle brands, dealerships</li>
            <li>Financial services — wealth management, private banking, insurance</li>
            <li>Travel — resort destinations, airlines, cruise lines</li>
            <li>Real estate — luxury home developers, realtors</li>
            <li>Healthcare — private clinics, dental, vision care</li>
            <li>Home improvement — premium renovation, landscaping, smart home</li>
            <li>Food and beverage — restaurants, wine, spirits</li>
            <li>Local services — businesses near your course that serve your membership</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="factors-box">
        <h3>Revenue factors</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Membership size and guest volume</strong> — more visitors = more impressions = more ad revenue</li>
          <li><strong>Market</strong> — courses in major metro areas attract more advertising demand</li>
          <li><strong>Course profile</strong> — private clubs command premium rates due to audience demographics</li>
          <li><strong>Number of screens</strong> — more screens capture more of the clubhouse traffic</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="clublink-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Our golf course partnership: ClubLink</h2>
      <p>SDN operates screens in <strong>24 ClubLink golf courses</strong> across Ontario — the largest private golf course network in Canada. This partnership demonstrates how golf course digital advertising works at scale:</p>

      <div class="clublink-features">
        <div class="feature">Screens installed in every clubhouse at no cost to ClubLink</div>
        <div class="feature">National brand campaigns run alongside local business advertising</div>
        <div class="feature">Members benefit from useful content (weather, sports, course info)</div>
        <div class="feature">Revenue flows monthly with no effort from course staff</div>
      </div>

      <p class="expansion-note">We're expanding our golf network beyond ClubLink and looking for additional course partners across Canada — private clubs, resort courses, and premium public courses.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="difference-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>What makes SDN different for golf courses</h2>
      <p>Traditional golf course advertising usually means static sponsor boards in the parking lot or paper posters in the locker room. SDN is fundamentally different:</p>

      <div class="difference-grid">
        <div class="diff-item">
          <strong>Digital, not static</strong>
          <span>4K screens with dynamic, rotating content instead of faded sponsor boards</span>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-item">
          <strong>National advertisers</strong>
          <span>Access to major brand budgets, not just local sign sales</span>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-item">
          <strong>Zero cost</strong>
          <span>SDN pays for everything; your course pays nothing</span>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-item">
          <strong>Zero effort</strong>
          <span>No selling, no installation logistics, no maintenance</span>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-item">
          <strong>Useful content</strong>
          <span>Weather, scores, and course info that members actually want</span>
        </div>
        <div class="diff-item">
          <strong>Revenue sharing</strong>
          <span>Guaranteed monthly payments</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <h2>Apply to add screens to your clubhouse</h2>
    <p>If your golf course is in a Canadian market with active membership or strong guest traffic, we'd like to discuss a partnership. Complete our application and we'll respond within two business days.</p>
    <a href="/venues/apply/" class="btn-white">Apply now</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

